oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Pulaski town square
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of the east side of the town square in Pulaski. Some of the shops include Buggie's Iron and Hardware, a drugstore, and a bakery. Several people and horses are standing in front of the shops.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Plazas; Stores & shops
